external_knowledge:
- "top 10 employees" refers to the employees with the highest average work-life balance ratings;
- "work-life balance" is a measure of how well an employee manages their personal and professional responsibilities;
- "self-ratings" are the personal assessments provided by employees about their own performance or satisfaction.

- "Top 3" refers to the highest-ranked departments in each category;
- "Job satisfaction," "environment satisfaction," and "work-life balance" are ratings provided by employees;
- The rankings are based on the average scores within each department.

- 'above-average' refers to ratings higher than the average ratings for their department;
- 'self-ratings' are the ratings given by employees to themselves;
- 'work-life balance ratings' are the ratings of the employee's work-life balance.

- 'Stars that joined the constellation of the company' refers to employees hired between 2018 and 2020;
- 'Luminaries' refers to employees with an average self-rating greater than 4;
- 'Shone particularly bright' refers to having a high self-rating;
- 'Annual reviews' are the review periods of the performance evaluations.

- 'Highly satisfied' refers to an overall satisfaction score greater than 3, which is calculated as the average of environment, job, and relationship satisfaction;
- 'Completed more than two training programs' refers to employees who have finished at least three training programs within the year;
- 'High ratings from both managers and themselves' means an average rating greater than 3 from both manager and self-assessments.

- 'Beacons of happiness' refers to departments with high average job satisfaction;
- 'Shines brighter than a score of 4' implies an average job satisfaction greater than 4;
- 'Performance reviews' are evaluations of employee job satisfaction.

- "blossomed like flowers" refers to employees who have shown significant growth and development;
- "richer than $100,000" indicates a department with a budget exceeding $100,000;
- "average self-assessments" refers to the average self-rating given by the employee;
- "work-life balance ratings" refers to the average rating of the employee's work-life balance.

- 'training opportunities taken' refers to the number of training sessions an employee has completed within the year;
- 'average training opportunities' is the mean number of training sessions taken by employees in the same department;
- 'self-rating' is the employee's self-assessment of their performance;
- 'work-life balance rating' is a measure of how well an employee balances their work and personal life.

sql:
SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN pr.self_rating > 4 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / COUNT(DISTINCT pr.employee_id)) * 100 AS percentage_of_employees_with_high_self_rating
FROM performance_reviews pr;

external_knowledge:
- Active employees are those who are currently employed and active in the system (`is_active = 1`);
- The most recent performance review is identified by the highest `review_date` for each employee;
- The metaphor of a garden of employee growth is used to represent the continuous development and evaluation of employees within the organization.

- "Fertile departments" refer to departments with high average satisfaction scores;
- "Nurturing" implies a positive and supportive work environment;
- "Collective happiness" includes average scores for environment satisfaction, job satisfaction, relationship satisfaction, and work-life balance.

- 'Vibrant flowers' metaphorically refers to employees who perform exceptionally well in multiple aspects of their work environment and personal evaluations;
- 'Standing tall' represents a high rank in the performance metrics;
- 'Grand garden of our corporate ecosystem' refers to the company or organization.

- 'High-performing employees' are those who have completed more than two trainings and have average ratings above 3 in work-life balance, self-ratings, manager ratings, and all departmental satisfaction ratings;
- 'Significant amount of training' refers to having completed more than two training sessions;
- 'Good work-life balance' is defined as having an average work-life balance rating greater than 3;
- 'High satisfaction' is defined as having average ratings greater than 3 in self-ratings, manager ratings, and all departmental satisfaction ratings (environment, job, relationship, work-life balance).

- 'Active sales professionals' refers to employees who are currently active and work in the Sales department;
- 'Embraced personal growth opportunities' means they have taken at least one training opportunity within the year;
- 'This year' refers to the current calendar year.

- "bloom the brightest" refers to the departments with the highest average satisfaction scores;
- "level of contentment" refers to the average satisfaction score;
- The average satisfaction score is calculated by averaging the environment, job, and relationship satisfaction ratings.

sql:
SELECT e.employee_name, pr.self_rating, pr.manager_rating
FROM performance_reviews pr
JOIN employees e ON pr.employee_id = e.employee_id;
